Questions:
What is the primary objective of the research study titled "Low vs Standard Dose Indocyanine Green in the Identification of Biliary Anatomy Using Near-Infrared Fluorescence Imaging"?
A) To compare the effectiveness of two different doses of a medical dye in improving the visibility of liver and bile ducts during surgery;
B) To evaluate the safety of using indocyanine green (ICG) in patients with a history of shellfish and iodine allergy;
C) To determine the cost-effectiveness of using near-infrared fluorescence imaging in routine surgeries;
D) To assess the patient recovery time when using standard versus low doses of ICG.

Correct answer: A) To compare the effectiveness of two different doses of a medical dye in improving the visibility of liver and bile ducts during surgery.

Which aspect of the study is considered experimental according to the new consent form?
A) The use of ultrasound or x-ray imaging during surgery;
B) The administration of a standard 2.5 mg dose of indocyanine green (ICG);
C) The comparison between a standard dose and a lower dose of indocyanine green (ICG) for imaging;
D) The routine pre-operative and post-operative care including blood tests and liver biopsies.

Correct answer: C

How will the research team ensure the confidentiality of your identifiable health information during the study?
A) By publishing all your personal health information online; 
B) By sharing your information with any interested third party without consent;
C) By assigning a unique study code to each patient and saving data on a secure server after removing identifiers;
D) By allowing all hospital staff access to the research data without restrictions.

Correct answer: C) By assigning a unique study code to each patient and saving data on a secure server after removing identifiers.
